#Data viz and wrangling

```{r}
library(tidyverse)
library(skimr)
```
```{r}
fastfood<-read_csv("https://raw.githubusercontent.com/rfordatascience/tidytuesday/master/data/2018/2018-09-04/fastfood_calories.csv")
```

#Working with different data types

```{r}
skim(fastfood)
```

# We need to convert our variables
```{r}

fastfood$restaurant<-as_factor(fastfood$restaurant)
fastfood$item<-as_factor(fastfood$item)
fastfood$salad<-as_factor(fastfood$salad)
skim(fastfood)
```
```{r}
fastfood <- fastfood %>% replace(is.na(.), 0)
```

Create two new variables:

Read about `cut_number()` function using to assist and add a new variable to the dataset `calories_type` arguments to add labels `c("low", "med", "high")` and make the dataset ordered

```{r}
fastfood <- fastfood %>%
  mutate(calories_type = cut_number(calories, 3, labels = c("low", "med", "high")))
```


```{r}
fastfood <- fastfood[order(fastfood$calories_type),]
head(fastfood)
```

# Adding facet wrap
```{r}
fastfood %>%
  ggplot(aes(
    x = calories_type,
    fill = calories_type
  ))+
  geom_bar(width=0.75)+
  facet_wrap(~ restaurant)+
  coord_flip()+
  theme_minimal()+
  scale_fill_manual(values=c("#FFEF77","#FFAC25","#F85720"))
  
```

